      {
        "location": "default-bridge-network",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Default bridge network",
        "text": "<p>The simplest way to run canon-proxy in Docker. Docker's iptables MASQUERADE rewrites the container source IP to the host's LAN IP, so the camera sees a same-subnet connection and accepts the PTP/IP handshake.</p> <p>Persist the database</p> <p>Set <code>database.dsn: /data/canon-proxy.db</code> in your <code>config.yaml</code> so the SQLite database is written inside the <code>/data</code> volume. Using the default <code>./canon-proxy.db</code> path places the file in the container filesystem and the database will be lost when the container is recreated.</p> <pre><code>docker run --rm \\\n  -v \"$(pwd)/config.yaml:/app/config.yaml:ro\" \\\n  -v canon-proxy-data:/data \\\n  -p 9090:9090 \\\n  ghcr.io/pacorreia/canon-proxy:latest\n</code></pre>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "host-network-alternative",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Host network (alternative)",
        "text": "<p>Use <code>--network host</code> if bridge NAT is not available (e.g. certain NAS environments or when the camera requires strict same-subnet enforcement):</p> <pre><code>docker run --rm \\\n  --network host \\\n  -v \"$(pwd)/config.yaml:/app/config.yaml:ro\" \\\n  -v canon-proxy-data:/data \\\n  ghcr.io/pacorreia/canon-proxy:latest\n</code></pre>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "docker-compose",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Docker Compose",
        "text": "<pre><code>services:\n  canon-proxy:\n    image: ghcr.io/pacorreia/canon-proxy:latest\n    ports:\n      - \"9090:9090\"\n    volumes:\n      - ./config.yaml:/app/config.yaml:ro\n      - canon-proxy-data:/data\n    restart: unless-stopped\n\nvolumes:\n  canon-proxy-data:\n</code></pre>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "kubernetes-helm",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Kubernetes (Helm)",
        "text": "",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "add-the-oci-chart",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Add the OCI chart",
        "text": "<pre><code>helm install canon-proxy \\\n  oci://ghcr.io/pacorreia/charts/canon-proxy \\\n  --version 0.1.0 \\\n  --namespace canon-proxy \\\n  --create-namespace \\\n  -f my-values.yaml\n</code></pre>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "key-values",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Key values",
        "text": "<pre><code># my-values.yaml\n\nconfig:\n  camera:\n    host: \"192.168.2.70\"\n    port: 15740\n    poll_interval: 5s\n  upload:\n    workers: 1\n    backend: smb\n  web:\n    listen: \":9090\"\n\n# SMB credentials — stored in a Secret\nsecret:\n  smb:\n    password: \"mysecretpassword\"\n\n# Persistent volume for the SQLite database\npersistence:\n  enabled: true\n  size: 1Gi\n\n# Traefik IngressRoute\ningress:\n  enabled: true\n  host: \"canon-proxy.example.com\"\n  tls: true\n\n# Set to true only if your camera is NOT reachable via the cluster CNI.\n# When true, the pod shares the node's network namespace.\nhostNetwork: false\n</code></pre> <p>hostNetwork and camera access</p> <p>If the Canon camera is on the same LAN as your Kubernetes nodes but not reachable from the pod network (no routing / CNI isolation), set <code>hostNetwork: true</code> to share the node's network namespace. The camera will then see the node's real IP.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "upgrade",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Upgrade",
        "text": "<pre><code>helm upgrade canon-proxy \\\n  oci://ghcr.io/pacorreia/charts/canon-proxy \\\n  --version 0.2.0 \\\n  --reuse-values\n</code></pre>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "building-from-source",
        "level": 2,
        "title": "Building from source",
        "text": "<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/pacorreia/canon-proxy.git\ncd canon-proxy\n\n# Build for the local OS\nCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -o canon-proxy ./cmd/canon-proxy\n\n# Cross-compile for Linux ARM64\nCGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o canon-proxy-linux-arm64 ./cmd/canon-proxy\n</code></pre>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "build-the-docker-image",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Build the Docker image",
        "text": "<pre><code>docker build -t canon-proxy:local .\n</code></pre> <p>The Dockerfile uses a distroless nonroot runtime image — no shell, minimal attack surface.</p>",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      }
